cy-improve-architecture — THIRD-PARTY NOTICES

This Compozy extension is a port of open-source skills authored by Matt Pocock
to the Compozy workflow, adapted and extended as described below, used under
the MIT License.

Upstream source: https://github.com/mattpocock/skills

Adapted skills:
  - improve-codebase-architecture  (deep/shallow-module audit, deletion test, HTML report)
  - codebase-design                (deep-module vocabulary and design-it-twice guidance)
  - domain-modeling                (glossary upkeep)

The optional interactive grilling enhancement may use Matt Pocock's grill-me
skill from the same source when it is installed; a built-in interrogation runs
without it.

The Compozy adaptation adds the durable, @import-able .compozy/ARCHITECTURE.md
depth map and its Markdown report twin, a test-only grammar validator (archmap),
packaging/install tests, and a model-backed evaluation harness.

